Useful VSCode Shortcuts


**Navigation**
- `Ctrl+P` (Cmd+P) — Quick open file by name
- `Ctrl+Shift+P` (Cmd+Shift+P) — Command palette (access almost any command)
- `Ctrl+G` — Go to line
- `Ctrl+Tab` — Switch between open files
- `Ctrl+Shift+O` — Go to symbol (function/variable) in file
- `Ctrl+T` — Go to symbol across whole workspace
- `Alt+Left / Alt+Right` (Ctrl+-  / Ctrl+Shift+-) — Navigate back/forward through cursor history

**Editing**
- `Ctrl+D` — Select next occurrence of current word (great for multi-cursor renaming)
- `Ctrl+Shift+L` — Select all occurrences of current word
- `Alt+Click` (Option+Click) — Add a new cursor at click point
- `Ctrl+Alt+Up/Down` — Add cursor above/below
- `Shift+Alt+Up/Down` (Shift+Option+Up/Down) — Copy line up/down
- `Alt+Up/Down` (Option+Up/Down) — Move line up/down
- `Ctrl+Shift+K` — Delete entire line
- `Ctrl+/` — Toggle line comment
- `Shift+Alt+A` — Toggle block comment
- `Ctrl+Enter` — Insert line below without splitting current line
- `Ctrl+Shift+Enter` — Insert line above
- `Tab` / `Shift+Tab` — Indent / outdent selected line(s)

**Search & Replace**
- `Ctrl+F` — Find in file
- `Ctrl+H` — Replace in file
- `Ctrl+Shift+F` — Find across entire project
- `Ctrl+Shift+H` — Replace across entire project

**Code Understanding**
- `F12` — Go to definition
- `Alt+F12` — Peek definition (inline popup, no navigation)
- `Shift+F12` — Find all references
- `Ctrl+.` (Cmd+.) — Quick fix / show code actions
- `F2` — Rename symbol (renames everywhere it's used)
- `Ctrl+K Ctrl+I` — Show hover info (docs/type info) at cursor

**Layout & Workflow**
- `Ctrl+\`` (Cmd+\`) — Toggle integrated terminal
- `Ctrl+B` — Toggle sidebar
- `Ctrl+\` — Split editor
- `Ctrl+1 / Ctrl+2 / Ctrl+3` — Jump to split pane 1/2/3
- `Ctrl+J` — Toggle panel (terminal/output/problems area)
- `Ctrl+K Z` — Zen mode (distraction-free)

**Multi-file / Project**
- `Ctrl+Shift+E` — Focus Explorer (file tree)
- `Ctrl+Shift+G` — Focus Source Control (git)
- `Ctrl+Shift+X` — Extensions panel
- `Ctrl+Shift+M` — Problems panel (errors/warnings)

